Matt Blaze (mab@research.att.com) writes:

> the underlying cipher.  Things like PGP encrypt individual files (and,
> I assume, data streams) on demand, while things like Diskreet present
> a file system interface that includes encryption as a basic feature.

Minor nit-pick - Diskreet provides both features. It comes as two
files - DISKREET.SYS is a device driver which supports an encrypted
filesystem, and DISKREET.EXE is a stand-alone program which can be
used to encrypt files.

